    "created_at": "2012-09-28T20:44:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-09-28T20:44:38Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The `from __future__ import absolute_import` lines were created by writing a custom 2to3 fixer using support from [python-modernize](https://github.com/mitsuhiko/python-modernize).\n\n``` python\nfrom lib2to3 import fixer_base\nfrom libmodernize import add_future\n\nclass FixAbsoluteImportFuture(fixer_base.BaseFix):\n\n    BM_compatible = True\n    PATTERN = \"\"\"\n    import_from< 'from' imp=any 'import' ['('] any [')'] >\n    |\n    import_name< 'import' imp=any >\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def start_tree(self, tree, name):\n        super(FixAbsoluteImportFuture, self).start_tree(tree, name)\n        self.skip = \"absolute_import\" in tree.future_features\n\n    def transform(self, node, results):\n        if not self.skip:\n            add_future(node, 'absolute_import')\n        self.skip = True\n```\n"
  },
