    "created_at": "2012-10-01T22:40:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-10-01T22:40:54Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The problem, of course, is that it is difficult to know where the future\nmatters, and trouble would only crop up in situations where a developer\nadded a new import statement expecting to get a global module and instead\ngot a local module -- e.g, a `import io` from any file in `IPython/utils`.\n\nI think we should seriously consider a default set of `__future__` import\nstatements in all modules, regardless of use, as a way of enforcing coding\nstyle best practices and future compatibility.\n\nNonetheless, I'm happy to remove the \"noise\" for now.\n"
  },
